sudo visudo -f /etc/sudoers
• Opens the sudoers configuration file safely using visudo.
• Defines who can run what commands, as which user, on which machine.



Sudo Rule for a User : username ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL
• User username can run any command as any user/group on any host.

Restricted sudo (specific binaries only) : username ALL=(root) NOPASSWD:/usr/bin/cat,/usr/bin/apt,/usr/bin/ls

• User can run only these commands as root.
• No password required.
• sudo will not work for any other commands.




Sudo Rule for a Group : %groupname ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL
• All members of groupname have full sudo privileges.

Restricted sudo for a group : %groupname ALL=(root) NOPASSWD:/usr/bin/cat,/usr/bin/apt,/usr/bin/ls
• Group members can execute only the specified binaries as root.
• sudo access is limited strictly to those commands.
